article.description: Davauhnte Turner had 16 points as Saint Peter's snapped its eight-game losing streak, beating Marist 65-59 on Friday night.
article.headline: Turner scores 16 to lead Saint Peter's over Marist 65-59
article.linkText: Turner scores 16 to lead Saint Peter's over Marist 65-59
article.story: POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y. -- Davauhnte Turner had 16 points as Saint Peter's snapped its eight-game losing streak, beating Marist 65-59 on Friday night. KC Ndefo had 13 points for Saint Peter's (7-20, 4-11 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Quinn Taylor added 10 points. Samuel Idowu had three blocks for the visitors. Brian Parker had 19 points for the Red Foxes (12-15, 7-8), whose four-game win streak was broken. Ryan Funk added 12 points. David Knudsen had seven rebounds. The Peacocks improve to 2-0 against the Red Foxes this season. Saint Peter's defeated Marist 72-63 on Jan. 13. Saint Peter's matches up against Niagara at home on Sunday. Marist plays Siena on the road on Sunday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap , using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
